The paper proposes a method to control overfitting in complex structure models, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis and empirical evaluations, which are common in the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely sub-category is computational linguistics (cs.CL), followed by machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
